      <abstract xml:lang="eng" xml:id="ProfileDescAbstractSchoolbook">
        <p>The history textbook was conceptualised for secondary stage II at grammar schools. It covers the period from the Reformation in the first half of the sixteenth century until the Enlieghtenment, and the Congress of Vienna in 1815. it is characterised by an uncommonly large number of illustrations and charts, which are included in almost every page for illustrative purposes.</p>
      </abstract>
      <abstract xml:lang="eng" xml:id="ProfileDescAbstractShort">
        <p>The Dutch artist Gerard Ter Borch based his 1670 historical painting on an event very important for his epoch and for the Dutch Republic: the Peace of Münster in 1648, which ended the Thirty Years' War in Europe and the Dutch War of Independence against the Spanish Habsburgers.</p>
      </abstract>
      <abstract xml:lang="eng" xml:id="ProfileDescAbstractLong">
        <p>The Dutch artist Gerard Ter Borch based his 1670 historical painting on an event very important for his epoch and for the Dutch Republic: the Peace of Münster in 1648, which ended the Thirty Years' War in Europe and the Dutch War of Independence against the Spanish Habsburgers. The delegations from the Netherlands and Spain are picted during the swearing of the oath in the Münster town hall after the signing of seperate peace between Spain and the Netherlands on 15 May 1648.</p>
      </abstract>
